cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the application of deep learning-based methods, especially convolutional neural network-based (CNN-based) methods for remote sensing image scene classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an automatically architecture learning procedure for CNN, which involves the use of gradient descent, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of a learning strategy to discover the optimal set of parameters for a given dataset, which could also place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper also deals with remote sensing images, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category. Finally, the paper involves the use of an architecture generator to map the set of parameters into the CNN used in the experiments, which could also place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
